"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her first high school athlete\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2413}, {\"ngram\": \"the year award\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"the high school record books\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m hurdles\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2508}, {\"ngram\": \"a new world youth\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2602}, {\"ngram\": \"54.15s\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2612}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McLaughlin-Levrone was then eliminated before the final round and in an interview following the race, she vowed she would be back and ready to fight for a podium spot.\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McLaughlin-Levrone\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2676}, {\"ngram\": \"the final round\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2739}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"a podium spot\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the intervening years she improved her pace and developed a loose rivalry with fellow American Dalilah Muhammad who had claimed gold in the 400m hurdles in Rio.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2916, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996003732851313, \"rank\": 0.00016505576130600684, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2925, \"end\": 2941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dalilah Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\"}, {\"begin\": 2